content: I am a graduate student in data-centric engineering at the University of Cambridge supervised by Professor Mark Girolami. I am also affiliated with the data-centric engineering group at the Alan Turing Institute in London. Prior to Cambridge I was working as a Statistical Scientist at an AI startup in London. I completed my undergraduate studies in Statistics and Computer Science (known as ‘data science’) at the University of Warwick , where I received a first class honours degree. My full CV can be found here.
